    <p>
      <span style="border-top-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 0px; border-right-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-right-style: solid; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-left-style: solid; border-left-width: 0px; margin-top: 0px; color: black; font-family: __fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal"><font color="black" face="__fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" size="16px">While instances of insider trading challenge the notion of perfect market efficiency, they don't necessarily invalidate the concept of generally efficient markets. Markets can be efficient most of the time, with occasional inefficiencies that are typically short-lived as information becomes public and prices adjust.</font></span><font color="black" face="__fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" size="16px"><span style="border-top-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 0px; border-right-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-right-style: solid; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-color: rgb(229, 231, 235); border-left-style: solid; border-left-width: 0px; color: black; font-family: __fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal">The existence of some market inefficiencies actually helps maintain overall efficiency, as it provides incentives for market participants to seek out mispriced securities, thereby pushing prices toward their fair values</span></font>.<span style="color: black; font-family: __fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; display: inline !important; float: none"><font color="black" face="__fkGroteskNeue_598ab8, __fkGroteskNeue_Fallback_598ab8, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica Neue, Arial, Noto Sans, sans-serif, Apple Color Emoji, Segoe UI Emoji, Segoe UI Symbol, Noto Color Emoji" size="16px">In practice, markets likely fall somewhere between perfect efficiency and complete inefficiency. The degree of efficiency can vary across different markets, securities, and time periods. Regulatory bodies play a crucial role in maintaining market integrity and promoting efficiency by enforcing rules against insider trading and mandating timely disclosure of material information.</font></span>
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
